>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Main Technical Index</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p>Specially designed for connecting the low-voltage side of large power transformers to isolated phase bus ducts, these bushings handle exceptionally high currents with utmost reliability.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Product Advantages</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p><strong>Extreme Current Rating:</strong> Engineered for currents up to 40kA with stable thermal and electrical performance.</p>
    <p><strong>Solid Insulation Choice:</strong> Available in robust RIF or RIP insulation technology.</p>
    <p><strong>Superior to Conventional Designs:</strong> Unlike traditional porcelain bushings that rely on oil for insulation (prone to uneven field distribution and oil leakage), our solid dielectric design ensures consistent performance and absolute containment.</p>
    <p><strong>Custom Design:</strong> Built to match specific bushing and busbar interface requirements.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Suitable Service Conditions for Bushings</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p><strong>Ambient Temperature:</strong> Suitable for -50 °C to +50 °C.</p>
    <p><strong>Installation Angle:</strong> Can be installed at any angle.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Ordering Information</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p>When placing an order, please specify rated voltage, rated current, and busbar interface requirements. Custom designs available for specific transformer manufacturers.</p>
  </div>

</ProductDetailLayout>
